":"Hadith on Food: The Prophet\u2019s family rarely ate to their fill","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 15, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The family of Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him,\u00a0never ate to their fill of wheat bread for three consecutive nights, ever since they had come to Medina, until he passed away. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6089, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2970 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34527,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/10\/28\/prophet-suffers-with-sahabah\/","url_meta":{"origin":285,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet suffers in poverty with his companions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 28, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Talhah reported: We complained about hunger to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and we lifted our garments to reveal stones tied to our stomachs, so the Messenger of Allah lifted his garment to reveal two stones. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2371 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34995,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/19\/prophet-feed-family\/","url_meta":{"origin":285,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet does not feed his family to their fill","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 19, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: By the One in whose hand is my soul, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, did not satiate his family with wheat bread for three consecutive nights until he departed from this world. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2976 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6640,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/18\/umar-hudud-suspended-famine\/","url_meta":{"origin":285,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Hudud: Punishment of theft suspended during famine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Yahya ibn Abi Kathir reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThe hand of the thief is not cut who steals a bundle of dates or in a year of famine.\u201d Source: Mus\u0323annaf Abd al-Razza\u0304q 18371 Al-Sa\u2019di reported: I asked Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah have\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26024,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/05\/prophet-suffers-hunger\/","url_meta":{"origin":285,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet suffers from hunger all day","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 5, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar reported: I saw the Messenger of Al